I am writing in response to the application for tenure-track fAssistant Professor position at the Department of Mathematics and Statistics,
 University of Ottawa,
 as advertised on MathJobs.org.
 Currently,
 I am
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent

\size large
an Assistant Professor of Mathematics,
 at Zu Chongzhi Center,
 Duke Kunshan University;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\size large
and also holding the Adjunct of the Faculty of Graduate Studies,
 Department of Mathematics and Statistics,
 Dalhousie University.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent

\size large
\begin_inset VSpace 10bp
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent

\size large
I am studying 
\emph on
Experimental Mathematics
\emph default
,
 namely,
 computer software (e.g.,
 Mathematica,
 SageMath,
 Maple,
 etc.
 ) and algorithms play important role to investigate,
 observe,
 and proof certain results.
 Mainly,
 I am interested in problems in Number Theory,
 Combinatorics,
 Symbolic Computation,
 Special Functions,
 and Probabilistic Methods.
 
\begin_inset Note Note
status collapsed

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
\align left

\emph on
the Bernoulli symbol 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{\mathcal{B}}=iL_{B}-1/2$
\end_inset

 and the Euler symbol 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{E}=iL_{E}-1/2$
\end_inset

:
 
\emph default
two random variables,
 for 
\begin_inset Formula $L_{B}\sim\pi\sech^{2}\left(\pi t\right)/2$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $L_{E}\sim\sech\left(\pi t\right)$
\end_inset


\family roman
\series medium
\shape up
\size normal
\emph off
\bar no
\strikeout off
\uuline off
\uwave off
\noun off
\color none
 on 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

,
 and 
\begin_inset Formula $i^{2}=1$
\end_inset

.
 The method involves probabilistic method and symbolic computation,
 with applications in extended polynomials,
 multiple zeta values,
 orthogonal polynomials,
 Hankel determinants,
 etc.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
\align left

\emph on
symbolic and algorithmic computations
\emph default
,
 especially with applications in special functions,
 numbers theory,
 and combinatorics.
 This includes
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
symbolic summation and integration:
 for example,
 the method of brackets,
 which is a symbolic integration method,
 based on Ramanujan's master theorem,
 with only six rules to compute 
\begin_inset Formula $\int_{0}^{\infty}f\left(x\right)dx$
\end_inset

 in terms of series.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\noindent
\align left
quantum algorithms:
 and I mainly focus on matrix representations of certain functions,
 that are highly related to quantum gates;
 and implementation of algorithms:via,
 e.g.,
 Python,
 Mathematica,
 Qiskit,
 and Quitip.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\emph on
differential and information geometry
\emph default
:
 in only two directions:
 finding the shortest quantum gate path via geodesics framework,
 and the study of family of hyperbolic secant distributions,
 which includes the density functions of both Bernoulli and Euler symbols,
 mentioned above.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset VSpace 10bp
\end_inset


\end_layout

